		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://thevoiceswithin.com/?p=114</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[A: &#8220;Do you believe in God?&#8221; B: &#8220;I believe in a God that makes people happy all the time.&#8221; &#8220;What about the God that gives people their problems?&#8221; &#8220;I said I believe in one that makes people happy.&#8221; &#8220;Isn&#8217;t happiness subjective? Don&#8217;t you think you are doing a monstrously preposterous job of including subjectivity to [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A: &#8220;Do you believe in God?&#8221;</p>
<p>B: &#8220;I believe in a God that makes people happy all the time.&#8221;</p>
<p>&#8220;What about the God that gives people their problems?&#8221;</p>
<p>&#8220;I said I believe in one that makes people happy.&#8221;</p>
<p>&#8220;Isn&#8217;t happiness subjective? Don&#8217;t you think you are doing a monstrously preposterous job of including subjectivity to something that&#8217;s being treated as an object?&#8221;</p>
<p>&#8220;No, I don&#8217;t. I would rather believe in a God that&#8217;s impartial. I can&#8217;t bear the poverty around me. There is so much that is being denied to common people. Only a revolution in the hearts, minds and hands of the people is going to change all this.&#8221;</p>
<p>&#8220;Oh yeah? So do you mean to say you are an atheist? A God that does only makes people happy is non-existent. It would be one helluva boring job even if it were the one. So, that would make you an atheist. A peasant can become a billionaire if only he chooses to. What do you think of human choice? Don&#8217;t you think you and I can change the world if only we wished it?&#8221;</p>
<p>&#8220;Well..&#8221;</p>
<p>*End of Conversation*</p>
<p>B radically shifts his views and immediately changes his religious views on his Facebook page to &#8220;Atheist&#8221;. This of course reflects B&#8217;s <em>choice</em> in changing his religious views on social networking sites where he thinks majority of his friends will respect his &#8220;newfound&#8221; wisdom. The lecture A gave on human choice fell on ears superbly insulated from Knowledge.</p>
<p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</p>
<p>N looks expectantly as A approaches her with a rose.</p>
<p>&#8220;A, I love you.&#8221;</p>
<p>&#8220;I think I like you too but I need some time to decide..&#8221;</p>
<p>&#8220;I have penned a poem for you, N. May I recite it?&#8221;</p>
<p>&#8220;Oh, of course. You are the romantic kind, aren&#8217;t you? *flirtatious look*</p>
<p>&#8220;You are..&#8221; A confidently begins, and the curves of his lips herald danger.</p>
<p>&#8220;You are like the pearl from the distant oceans I wish to see bound to my chains, like the serene moon that has a perpetual smirk on her face, like the lotus flower that is too proud to let water stick to it, the clever vixen that has five fabulous senses&#8230;&#8221;</p>
<p>*End of conversation*</p>
<p>Non verbal blows speak louder than verbal ones. Period.</p>
<p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</p>
<p>Post Script: The post will be updated as and when I find get such &#8216;inspiring&#8217; thoughts.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
