			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Dear language,</p>
<p>The subtle symbols you use to bind me with invisible threads in the form of ideas overwhelm me, making me wonder if I will be able to connect the dots of the fine fabric with a steady mind not getting lured by the breezy organization of wavelengths that at times tempts me into finding illusory patterns, blocking the beauty of what lies beneath. Connecting the dots is one thing, but finding the right instrumentation to do so is what makes the task look complex, or rather seemingly simplistic to one that intentionally misses the dots, not willing to let the instrumentation at hand exploit the freedom he/she gives it. You subject me to beliefs I have never had the pleasure of thinking about&#8211; that of determined freewill. How then can I explain my being totally dependent on you for even giving an expression to whatever my time-bound mind indulges haphazardly in? I am lost in your world of mazes, willingly letting you take me places- be it the circuitous path that you subject me to or the cheerful route behind (if looked closely) and beyond which lies your true identity&#8211; your unique personality; that which I will, for eternity, be seeking.</p>
<p>With the kind of love that can never be expressed within your realms,</p>
<p>R</p>
]]></content:encoded>
